# Milestone 100: keep byte-identity test fixtures + canonical-output
# artifacts on LF regardless of the operator's git autocrlf setting.
# On Windows, git's default `core.autocrlf=true` would convert LF →
# CRLF on checkout, which breaks `cdx_regression` / `spdx_regression` /
# `spdx3_regression` byte-equality assertions (the goldens were minted
# on Linux with LF; the SBOM emitter writes LF on every host).

# All SBOM goldens — pin to LF.
mikebom-cli/tests/fixtures/golden/**/*.json text eol=lf

# JSON files in general default to LF; safer than relying on host
# autocrlf semantics for any committed JSON fixture.
*.json text eol=lf

# Rust source files — LF everywhere. cargo + rustfmt assume LF.
*.rs text eol=lf
